About
Dubai-based Children's City is the first educational city in the United Arab Emirates devoted to children between two and fifteen years old where they can investigate, explore, play, discover, and learn about the world in which we live. The Children's City is specially designed for children to interact and discover together in family and school groups. It contains several exhibits and programs like a nature center, space exploration, human body, planetarium, the way we live and international culture as well as toddlers area. In addition, Children's City presents daily educational workshops throughout the year at the different galleries or in the purpose-built halls and entertainment programs at the Children's City Theater for school students, children and families.
Duration: 2-3 hours

  • AJD28
    Gujarat, India467 contributions
    Educational and Informative - with scope and capacity to become a fantastic venue but lacking some creativity
    A good entertaining venue, particularly during the summer. The exhibits are educational and informative. The planetarium also incorporates very interesting materials showcasing videos purpose made for young children to educate in a fun way. There was unfortunately not much guidance from staff to engage the children, which other locations in Dubai benefit from - i.e. where staff direct and interact with children and bring exhibits to life. I feel more could be done with the expansive space available too to really make this is a must-go-to venue. At the moment, it is somewhat treated as an add-on if visiting the dolphinarium but they could invest some creativity into making this a standalone visit. Pricing is reasonable but perhaps on the high side considering what is currently offered. My daughter was able to do some facepainting which she thoroughly enjoyed and there is a small softplay for very young children too.
    Visited July 2024
    Traveled with family
    Written July 25, 2024
